To set up the project, follow these steps:

Run npm install in the project directory to install all necessary dependencies.

Create a .env file at the root of the project directory. This file will store your environment variables. Add the following variables to it:



NODE_ENV=development
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster-url>.abpxecs.mongodb.net/<database-name>?retryWrites=true&w=majority
Replace <username>, <password>, <cluster-url>, and <database-name> with the appropriate values for your MongoDB Atlas account.

Create a .gitignore file at the root of the project directory. This file will tell Git to ignore certain files when committing changes. Add the following lines to it:



node_modules
.env
This will tell Git to ignore the node_modules directory and the .env file.